<p>As I stated earlier, it is wonderfully liberating to be less attached to my phone. Though it may involve some effort to adopt such an attitude, it is surely worth attempting. To take it even further, I would argue that regularly spending time in wild places <em>without</em> cellular reception (such as the backcountry) is one of the best possible things to do with your time.</p>
